<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-11-22T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-11-22T09:00:00-05:00" n="747" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d747">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">767.68119/178: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Special Mission at
                                        Lausanne</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Lausanne</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-11-22T15:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">November
                                            22, 1922—3 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 8:15
                                    p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>11. The powers will not be inclined to ask for measures of relief for
                                the Armenians which would involve territorial sacrifices by Turkey,
                                as Angora objects intensely to any reduction of its territory to
                                form areas of refuge for minorities. To what extent should we go in
                                raising and supporting a point which may not be accepted and which
                                will arouse Turkey’s resentment?</p>
                            <closer><signed>
                                    <list>
                                        <item><hi rend="smallcaps">Child</hi></item>
                                        <item><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></item>
                                    </list></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>